imdb.title: Sengoku basara
imdb.plot: In the age of the Warring Countries, Japan was fragmented in semi-independent provinces, governed by feudal lords or daimyo, who confronted each other in an endless struggle for power. Ambitious daimyos from every corner of the Ar...

episodes.title: Ransei futatabi! Rekkai butei Toyotomi Hideyoshi kourin!
episodes.plot: Old rivalries resume at Kawanakajima as Sanada Yukimura battles Date Masamune and Takeda Shingen squares off against Uesugi Kenshin. Meanwhile, the warlord Toyotomi Hideyoshi seeks ultimate domination in order to unify Japan.

episodes.title: Rosuto migi me wa, Gashed doragon wa e modoru yo
episodes.plot: Under attack from all sides, Date Masamune is at a severe disadvantage without his strategist. Meanwhile, Takeda Shingen and Sanada Yukimura are on the move and preparing to outflank Toyotomi.

episodes.title: Keiji tai Toshiie! Tetorigawa ni musebu yuzurenu omoi!
episodes.plot: Uesugi Kenshin faces Maeda Toshiie's invading army! Meanwhile, in the north, Date Masamune prepares to engage Katakura Kojuro, but finds one more obstacle in his way.

episodes.title: Seigan no kokuin! Dokuganryuu tai gunshin hitotoribashi no taiji!
episodes.plot: When Date's path is blocked by Uesugi, he has a chance to reflect on the history he shares with Katakura. Meanwhile, Toyotomi prepares to invade Shikoku, and Sanada realizes that time is running out.

episodes.title: Kyoui no Toyotomi Moori doumei! Unabara o saku wa no gouken!!
episodes.plot: Toyotomi Hideyoshi takes on Chosokabe's seafaring fortress, the Fugaku. Meanwhile, Sanada is compelled to stray from his mission once again, and Keiji reunites with his aunt and uncle in Kaga.

episodes.title: Sainantan-Satsuma no Chi e! Yukimura, Aratanaru Otoko no Deai!
episodes.plot: While traveling to Osaka, Date encounters both Kai and Takeda. Meanwhile, Sanada is still shaken by Oyamada's death, but presses on to Satsuma in order to carry out his mission.

episodes.title: Tomogaki to no Kanashiki Saikai Môshû Kizamareshi Hi no Kioku!
episodes.plot: Keiji reflects on the long history he shares with Toyotomi. Meanwhile, Sanada is allowed an opportunity to get to know Miyamoto and Shimazu better, and also gains some surprising insight into Mori.

episodes.title: Fukkatsu no Wakaki Tora! Kaizô Daiyôsai-Nichirin no Kyôi, Higashi e!!
episodes.plot: As Date and Chosokabe adjust their plans to attack Osaka, Mori plots to attack Toyotomi from the west. Meanwhile, Takeda and Uesugi attempt to outmaneuver Toyotomi in the east.

episodes.title: Ryûko, Itadaki no Chikai! Atsuki Mirai e Kakeru Tamashii!!
episodes.plot: The action is over-the-top as Date and Yukimura take on a group of disguised fighters. While Date may realize the the masked men are actually Sasuke, Takeda, and Kojuro, Yukimura appears to have no clue.

episodes.title: Sôku: Shukumei no kaikô!
episodes.plot: Two of the mightiest warlords of ancient Japan, Takeda Shingen and Uesugi Kenshin, set aside their rivalry to unite against the forces of Date Masamune.

episodes.title: Senritsu! Okehazama no sôgû
episodes.plot: Sanada and Date rush to claim the same prize: Imagawa's head. A clash erupts between the two warriors, but before one can declare victory, their battle is interrupted by a horrifying presence.

episodes.title: Fûraibô Maeda Keiji!
episodes.plot: Free-spirited Keiji hopes to build an alliance against the threat of the Demon Lord. His visit with Uesugi ends on a promising note - but his meeting with Date Masamune leads to a battle.

episodes.title: Nagashino-Shitaragahara no gisen
episodes.plot: As entire armies stand poised to attack, Takeda and Uesugi offer Tokugawa a final chance to join forces against Oda - but once his loyalties are decided, a ruthless betrayal soaks the battlefield in blood.

episodes.title: Sakareta kizuna Masamune kutsujoku no taikyaku
episodes.plot: After he rises to defend the honor of the fallen Azai, Date Masamune orders his forces to retreat. However, Sanada is shocked to discover it might already be too late for the warrior to survive.

episodes.title: Ryakudatsu no kyôyû! Sôryû gekka no shinken shôbu
episodes.plot: Matsunaga takes three of Date's men hostage and demands a ransom of rare and valuable weaponry. Katakura sets out to rescue the men - but he might not be able to do it alone.

episodes.title: Kai no tora, Midaigawa ni shisu!
episodes.plot: Oda's army is on the move in the south, while his most lethal assassins strike the opposition leaders of the east. As Takeda and Uesugi fight for their lives, many loyal to the alliance meet their demise.

episodes.title: Yukimura saikifunô!? Date-gun namida no kaisan!!
episodes.plot: With Takeda and Uesugi injured, the remaining alliance leaders plot their final assault against Oda. Even though the situation looks bleak, Date and Sanada prepare to face their destinies.

episodes.title: Setouchi no Gekitotsu! Hi o Fuku Umi no Daiyosai-Fugaku!!
episodes.plot: During the march to war against the Demon Lord: When Keiji visits Chosokabe and Mori to persuade them to join the alliance, Oda's minions arrive to issue a very serious threat.
